"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the `sns.lmplot` function within the `g.map()` method. The `g.map()` method is intended to apply a function that takes the data as its first argument, while `sns.lmplot` is a higher-level function that creates a new figure and does not return a callable that can be used in this context.\",\n  \"patch\": \"6c6\\n< g.map(sns.lmplot, 'total_bill', 'tip')\\n---\\n> g.map(sns.scatterplot, 'total_bill', 'tip')\\n> g.map_dataframe(sns.regplot, 'total_bill', 'tip')\"\n}"